[The 2012 SBV vector season in Europe is approaching its end. During 2012, the virus continued its spread within and beyond its 2011 boundaries. One of the countries into which the virus spread during 2012, where intensive surveillance has been undertaken, is Switzerland. According to the recent report of the Swiss Federal Veterinary Office (FVO), a large part of the country's susceptible animals have, by now, undergone infection; consequently, there is no point in continuing the SBV serosurvey.

Further information and a map (last updated 15 Oct 2012) are available at http://www.bvet.admin.ch/gesundheit_tiere/01065/04051/index.html?lang=de (in German). - Mod.AS]
